  "day": 36,
  "key": "day_36_jesus_tested_in_wilderness",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-15",
  "title": {
    "en": "Jesus Is Tested in the Wilderness"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "After his baptism, Jesus goes into the desert.",
      "There he is tested."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "fasting",
        "icon": "landscape",
        "label": { "en": "Forty Days in the Desert" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit,",
          "returned from the Jordan",
          "and was led by the Spirit in the desert,",
          "where for forty days he was tempted by the devil.",
          "He ate nothing during those days,",
          "and at the end of them he was hungry."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "bread",
        "icon": "restaurant",
        "label": { "en": "Stones to Bread" },
        "lines": [
          "The devil said to him,",
          "“If you are the Son of God,",
          "tell this stone to become bread.”",
          "Jesus answered,",
          "“It is written:",
          "‘Man does not live on bread alone.’”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "kingdoms",
        "icon": "public",
        "label": { "en": "All the Kingdoms" },
        "lines": [
          "The devil showed him all the kingdoms of the world.",
          "He said,",
          "“If you worship me,",
          "it will all be yours.”",
          "Jesus answered,",
          "“It is written:",
          "‘Worship the Lord your God",
          "and serve him only.’”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "temple",
        "icon": "account_balance",
        "label": { "en": "Do Not Test God" },
        "lines": [
          "The devil had him stand on the highest point of the temple.",
          "“If you are the Son of God,” he said,",
          "“throw yourself down from here.”",
          "Jesus answered,",
          "“It says:",
          "‘Do not put the Lord your God to the test.’”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "departure",
        "icon": "exit_to_app",
        "label": { "en": "The Devil Leaves" },
        "lines": [
          "When the devil had finished all this tempting,",
          "he left him",
          "until an opportune time."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you notice about how Jesus responds to testing—and what he refuses?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Luke 4:1–13"]
  }
}
